First Lady Melania Trump participated in a virtual roundtable with the Congressional Coalition on Adoption Institute's Foster Youth Intern Group. The roundtable included 12 foster youth interns, Health and Human Services Assistant Secretary Lynn Johnson, and other administration officials. The interns briefed the First Lady on their policy suggestions, which included increased funding for access to technology and broadband services, transitional housing, and access for social workers, particularly during the COVID-19 pandemic. Melania Trump emphasized the importance of their policy proposals and stated that taking care of America's children is a bipartisan effort. Assistant Secretary Johnson provided remarks on the mission and work of the Administration for Children and Families at the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. The First Lady concluded by thanking the interns and encouraging them to continue advocating for children and families.